Dart Sass 1.54.0

To install Sass 1.54.0, download one of the packages below and add it to your PATH, or see the Sass website for full installation instructions.

Changes

  • Deprecate selectors with leading or trailing combinators, or with multiple combinators in a row. If they're included in style rules after nesting is resolved, Sass will now produce a deprecation warning and, in most cases, omit the selector. Leading and trailing combinators can still be freely used for nesting purposes.

  • Add partial support for new media query syntax from Media Queries Level 4. The only exception are logical operations nested within parentheses, as these were previously interpreted differently as SassScript expressions.

title: fix: retryStrategy.Limit is now read properly for backoff strategy. Fixes #9170.
body:
Signed-off-by: Dillen Padhiar <dillen_padhiar@intuit.com>

Fixes #9170 

Previously, this if statement always evaluated to false if you set a `Limit` for `RetryStrategy` as the `retryStrategy.Limit.IntVal` always equaled 0. The appropriate way to get the integer value from a `intstr.IntOrString` is to use `IntValue` which returns an int we cast to `int32`. 

```
if time.Now().Before(waitingDeadline) && retryStrategy.Limit != nil && int32(len(node.Children)) <= 
    int32(retryStrategy.Limit.IntValue()) {
    woc.requeueAfter(timeToWait)
    retryMessage := fmt.Sprintf("Backoff for %s", humanize.Duration(timeToWait))
    return woc.markNodePhase(node.Name, node.Phase, retryMessage), false, nil
}
```

title: docs: remove false line from retry docs
body:
This small PR removes a line from the docs that threw me off for a couple of hours today. What the docs state here is false unfortunately, therefore this PR removes it from the docs.

Can be tested with the following examples:

```yaml
retryStrategy:
  retryPolicy: "Always"
  expression: 'lastRetry.status == "Failed" && asInt(lastRetry.exitCode) not in [-1,0,1] or lastRetry.status == "Error"'
  limit: 3
```
Submit a simple workflow with above retrypolicy and delete the pod while it's running, the workflow will do a retry.

```yaml
retryStrategy:
  expression: 'lastRetry.status == "Failed" && asInt(lastRetry.exitCode) not in [-1,0,1] or lastRetry.status == "Error"'
  limit: 3
```
Submit a simple workflow again with above retrypolicy and delete the pod while it's running, the workflow will fail immediately.
